---
layout: layout-base.njk
title: Best Canadian Cities for Tomatoes | GrowByDate Data Rankings
description: A GrowByDate Data Ranking comparing Canadian tomato locations by outdoor tomato fit, GDD margin, frost-free days, and variety flexibility.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/best-canadian-cities-for-tomatoes/"
---

{% set board = bestCanadianCitiesForTomatoes %}
{% set top = board.top %}
{% set hardest = board.hardest %}

<section class="card leaderboardHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">GrowByDate Data Ranking</p>
  <h1>Best Canadian Cities for Tomatoes</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Which Canadian locations in the current GrowByDate dataset give outdoor tomatoes the best shot? This ranking compares tomato fit by GDD margin, frost-free days, delay tolerance, and variety flexibility.
  </p>

  <div class="leaderboardStatGrid" aria-label="Ranking summary">
    {% if top %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Current leader</span>
        <strong>{{ top.cityName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ top.score }}/100 · {{ top.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if hardest %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Toughest current test</span>
        <strong>{{ hardest.cityName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ hardest.score }}/100 · {{ hardest.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Dataset</span>
      <strong>{{ board.entries.length }} locations</strong>
      <span>Published Canadian tomato crop-city pages</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>The ranking</h2>
  <p>
    Higher scores mean tomatoes have a more comfortable outdoor season in a typical year. Lower scores usually mean gardeners need faster varieties, timely indoor starts, warmer garden sites, or protection.
  </p>

  <div class="tableWrap leaderboardTableWrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rank</th>
          <th>Location</th>
          <th>Tomato fit</th>
          <th>GDD margin</th>
          <th>Frost-free days</th>
          <th>Best variety fit</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in board.entries %}
          <tr>
            <td><strong>#{{ row.rank }}</strong></td>
            <td>
              <a href="{{ row.url }}"><strong>{{ row.cityName }}</strong></a><br>
              <span class="small muted">{{ row.regionName }}, Canada</span>
            </td>
            <td>
              <strong>{{ row.score }}/100</strong><br>
              <span class="fitBadge fitBadge-{{ row.badgeClass }}">{{ row.label }}</span>
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if row.gddMargin >= 0 %}+{% endif %}{{ row.gddMargin }} GDD<br>
              <span class="small muted">{{ row.availableGddFromPlanting }} available / {{ row.targetGdd }} target</span>
            </td>
            <td>{{ row.frostFreeDays }}</td>
            <td>
              {% if row.fittingVarietyLabels.length %}
                {{ row.fittingVarietyLabels | join(", ") }}
              {% else %}
                No clear outdoor fit
              {% endif %}
            </td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card leaderboardCallout">
  <h2>What this ranking means</h2>
  <p>
    Tomatoes are one of the best crops for a city-vs-city data ranking because they are popular, frost-sensitive, and heavily affected by seasonal heat. A tomato page can look fine by calendar days alone, but GDD margin often tells a more useful story.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <p>{{ board.methodology }}</p>
  <p>{{ board.caveat }}</p>
  <p class="small">
    Data export: <a href="/assets/data/rankings/best-canadian-cities-for-tomatoes.json">Canadian tomato ranking JSON</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": {{ board.title | dump | safe }},
  "description": {{ board.description | dump | safe }},
  "url": "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/best-canadian-cities-for-tomatoes/",
  "numberOfItems": {{ board.entries.length }},
  "itemListElement": [
    {% for row in board.entries %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ row.rank }},
        "name": {{ (row.cityName ~ " tomato fit score") | dump | safe }},
        "url": {{ (site.url ~ row.url) | dump | safe }}
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  ]
}
</script>
